"a.有美德的；自命清高的 【英】 adj. 有美德的 (showing virtue); 【考】 反义词：nefarious( 邪恶的) 【记】 来自名词virtue（美 德） adj. 有美德的; 还有贞操的 【记】源于: virtue(n 美德; 优点) 【反】nefarious(adj 邪恶的); base(adj 卑鄙的) 无 virtuous (adj.)  c.1300, ""characterized by vigor or strength; having qualities befitting a knight; valiant, hardy, courageous;"" from Old French vertuos ""righteous; potent; of good quality; mighty, valiant, brave"" (12c.), from Late Latin virtuosus ""good, virtuous,"" from Latin virtus (see virtue). From mid-14c. in English as ""having beneficial or efficacious properties;"" late 14c. (of persons) as ""having excellent moral qualities; conforming to religious law."" Related: Virtuously; virtuousness."
